It consists of two layers of gravel, one for drainage and the other for separation and a large layer of sand that allows a water purification that is both healthy and economical.
Morocco, as a developing country still has problems concerning the distribution of water, as a large part of its population still lacks access to drinking water, which is estimated at 3.5 million in 2016 due with multiple.
The market is estimated at more than 13% of the Moroccan population. 
People from rural and urban areas both can buy the filter but especially the ones from rural areas who don't have access to clean water.

Our project offers a service with a more affordable price for students with only 15Dhs per kilo the equivalent of 8 washed, ironed and delivered T-shirts which is 4 times cheaper compared to other laundries.

How to participate in the cleanliness of my city?
1 – Claims :
Simply take a picture and share a polluting place or a tray that overflows to speed up the cleaning process. By means of your position, you provide the authorities in charge with roadmap that effectively leads to the place in question. This action will give you points of commitment citizen.
2 - Waste sorting :
When you participate in the sorting service, you will benefit, through our partners, of bags specific to the type of recyclable material. The harvest that you will carry out will also give you points of commitment citizen.
 The application offers to users a gift list.
high_concept: Participate in the cleanliness of your city.

We went with the idea that if we can guaranty safety to our users they do adopt the concept!
